&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ISLE OF WIGHT NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UNPLANNEDCARE GROUP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPIRATORY TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 – Full Time - 5 months fixed term/secondment – (Job share considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated NMC Nurse who is looking to develop their skills and knowledge in Respiratory medicine to work within the Respiratory team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to a short term and exciting development within the team, we are seeking to appoint a Respiratory Support Nurse to support the existing team in the delivery of inpatient and community care. You will be dealing with patient queries, seeing ward patients for inhaler technique etc doing some telephone reviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relevant training will be provided&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for this post will already be experienced in the care of patients with respiratory conditions, be able to think and act creatively, work positively with colleagues from a wide range of clinical backgrounds and be able to engage patients and their families as partners in the care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please telephone Sarah Kearney – Lead Respiratory Clinical Nurse Specialist on 01983 552190, or email to Sarah.Kearney@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
